<br>
Hey ALL!!<br>
<br>
The Raid is definitely going to take place in City of Mist (Kunark). Nearest bind spot (i think) is in Field of Bone at Kaesora entrance (we'll be meeting there). Bat wings are recommended for the walk to the City through Emerald Jungle.<br>
<br>
Items I need:<br>
I have two more &quot;pages&quot; to get there for my epic. 1 drops randomly off any mob and the other is a random drop off the &quot;Spectral Courier&quot; who is only level 35.<br>
<br>
Depending on a number of factors (amount of high levels that attend, amount of time we have left) I may extend the raid to kill Lord Ghiosk(also in City of Mist). He drops three books used in the following epic step. He's and undead mob that summons in the low 50's and some of his information can be found here:<br>
www.everlore.com/bestiary...BID=125693<br>
and here:<br>
eqbeastiary.allakhazam.co...ml?id=4563<br>
<br>
It looks as though the &quot;Black Reaver Evacing&quot; is his Placeholder. The area where he spawns can get pretty crazy with adds. Lots of 50+ friends are recommended, and ALL of Mystic Entity is invited. Everyone can contribute in one way or the other so please feel free to join us.<br>
<br>
Time and Participants needed:<br>
I know all this chaos is going to take place either on a Saturday or Sunday afternoon (not this weekend) Maybe December 1 or 2? I'm giving everyone plenty of time to get all your friends pumped up early  . I would like a minimum of 5 clerics, 2 *more* shamans, 3 druids, 5 50+ tank types, and a GREAT mix of casters (Enchanters are a necessity) if we are to take the Lord down, otherwise we can always just use the time to take as much of the City down as we can hehe.. I'm all up for that too.<br>
<br>
Groups:<br>
I'm planning my groups based on strategies that i have seen flaws in, or have completely failed. I expect to create all self sustaining groups meaning at least 1 buffer per two groups and each group will have at least 1 healer. (Non of this &quot;all tank&quot; group or &quot;Two enchanters in one group&quot; thing that i have seen in the past, hehehe). Buffers will be responsible for keeping their group(s) buffed from the *beginning* of the raid til the end.<br>
<br>
Looting:<br>
Loot rules are pretty basic.. All group leaders are responsible for looting (in no specific order).<br>
The pages and books obviously go to me. If dupe pages are found other shamans in raid may random for them (i think they are no drop so the random would have to take place on the spot. We'll have to be organized and quick) All coin will be split evenly amoung all participants. All items will be randomed first amoung classes that can use them. If there are no classes that can use them, or that do not want the item, the random will be opened up to all raid participants.<br>
<br>
I'll keep ya posted on any changes or a more specific time. It will be posted in PST.<br>
<br>
PLEASE post comments and offer suggestions.. This IS my first raid and I may be making terrible mistakes.. hehe. Thanx everyone.<br>
<br>
